# Global Cache Access

Shared datasets live in `providedIn: 'root'` services that hold a private
`BehaviorSubject` + a `...Loaded$` flag. The real HTTP call fires ONCE at
bootstrap/on-login (orchestrated in `app.component.ts`). Feature components
**read the cache** — they do not re-fetch it.

## Group A — leave alone (already correct)

States, Daily quote, Organization, Organization list, Branding.
Do not change how these are consumed.

## Group B — one sanctioned pattern, no exceptions

Offices, Accounting offices, Cost codes, Chart of accounts, Contacts, Features, Property codes, Reservation codes, and the office-selection stream.

### The pattern: `ensure...Loaded()` → live `getAll...()`

Check that the cache has a value, then subscribe and **stay subscribed until the
component dies**. This is the ONLY accepted way to load Group-B data:

```typescript
this.officeService.ensureOfficesLoaded(organizationId).pipe(take(1)).subscribe({
  next: () => {
    this.officeService.getAllOffices().pipe(takeUntil(this.destroy$)).subscribe(offices => {
      this.offices = offices;
      // ...map dropdown, clear load flag...
    });
  },
  error: () => { /* clear load flag */ }
});
```

Reference implementation: `accounting/invoices/invoice/invoice.component.ts` (`loadOffices`, `loadReservationCodes`, `loadCostCodes`).

### Formatting (non-negotiable)

The call chain — `service.method(...).pipe(...).subscribe(` — stays on **one
line regardless of length**. Only the callback bodies wrap.

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD
this.officeService.getAllOffices().pipe(takeUntil(this.destroy$)).subscribe(offices => {
  this.offices = offices;
});

// ❌ BAD — chain broken across lines
this.officeService
  .getAllOffices()
  .pipe(takeUntil(this.destroy$))
  .subscribe(offices => {
    this.offices = offices;
  });
```

## Banned for Group B

- **One-shot only** — `ensureOfficesLoaded().pipe(take(1))` with no follow-on
  live `getAll...()` subscription. You must subscribe and stay subscribed.
- **Sync snapshot as a load** — `getAllOfficesValue()`, `getAllAccountingOfficesValue()`,
  `getAllCostCodesValue()`, `getAllChartOfAccountsValue()`, `getAllContactsValue()`, `getSelectedOfficeIdValue()`
  used to populate component data.
- **Raw HTTP** — `getOffices()`, `getOfficesByOrganization()`, `loadAllOffices()`,
  `getAccountingOffices()`, `loadAllAccountingOffices()`, `loadAllCostCodes()`,
  `loadAllContacts()`, `loadAllFeatures()`, `getFeaturesByOrganization()`,
  `getPropertyCodes()`, `getReservationCodes()`, `loadAllPropertyCodes()`, `loadAllReservationCodes()` from a feature component.

### Inline sync reads inside event handlers

You cannot subscribe inside a click/save handler. Do **not** call a `...Value()`
accessor there. Instead keep the data live-subscribed into a field (per the
pattern above) and read the **field** in the handler:

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD — read the live-maintained field
onSave(): void {
  const office = this.offices.find(o => o.id === this.selectedOfficeId);
}

// ❌ BAD — snapshot accessor in a handler
onSave(): void {
  const office = this.officeService.getAllOfficesValue().find(o => o.id === ...);
}
```

## Office-selection stream

`getSelectedOfficeId$()` is a single-id stream (not a list, so there is no
`getAll`). Subscribe live and stay subscribed; this already matches the rule:

```typescript
this.globalSelectionService.getSelectedOfficeId$().pipe(skip(1), takeUntil(this.destroy$)).subscribe(officeId => {
  // re-scope screen to new office
});
```

Keep the selected office in a field via this subscription; read the field in
handlers instead of `getSelectedOfficeIdValue()`.

## Allowed raw-HTTP exceptions (only these three)

1. `office-list.component` — owning admin screen, refresh after edits.
2. `cost-codes.component` — owning admin screen, refresh after edits.
3. `user.component` `loadOfficesForUserOrganization()` — cross-org SuperAdmin path.

Any other raw fetch of Group-B data from a feature component is a violation.
